    <category lang="en-us">
      <language id="cat.soc.soc-clm" title="SUSE OpenStack Cloud Lifecycle Manager documentation">
        <p>
        Cloud Lifecycle Manager (CLM) was
        introduced in the SUSE OpenStack Cloud 8 release in 2018. Based on
        Ansible and taking some of the functionality of the HPE Helion
        Lifecycle Manager that SUSE acquired in 2017, it supports
        template-oriented deployments of larger clouds that can scale out
        without downtime.
      </p>
      </language>
      <language id="cat.soc.soc-crow" title="SUSE OpenStack Cloud Crowbar documentation">
        <p>
        Crowbar has been the deployment engine of choice for SUSE OpenStack
        Cloud prior to version 8. Based on Chef, Crowbar makes it fast and
        easy to deploy private cloud environments, and is better suited to
        smaller deployments.
      </p>
      </language>
